00:18:09.500 --> 00:18:15.500
So here, for example, I have specified that I want a sidebar with the title called filters.

00:18:15.500 --> 00:18:23.500
And then you may notice I have UI output filter UI, and I'm actually going to define this in the server.

00:18:23.500 --> 00:18:30.500
The reason for that is because I want my filters to be as updated with the data as I can.

00:18:30.500 --> 00:18:35.500
So if I add a new category or add a new status or something like that.

00:18:35.500 --> 00:18:41.500
And so I'm actually going to specify it later on when I have read the reactive data in.

00:18:41.500 --> 00:18:48.500
But I do want to specify that I want it up here in the UI.

00:18:48.500 --> 00:18:51.500
Next, I add a header.

00:18:51.500 --> 00:18:57.500
And then finally, the card that actually contains the calendar that I want to see.

00:18:57.500 --> 00:19:02.500
And then finally, the footer that I created up above.

00:19:02.500 --> 00:19:04.500
Now, here is the most critical part.

00:19:04.500 --> 00:19:06.500
We talked about reactivity earlier.

00:19:06.500 --> 00:19:12.500
So the server is where we actually build in reactivity for our shiny app.

00:19:12.500 --> 00:19:19.500
And the key takeaway for today is this pin reactive read function from pins.

00:19:19.500 --> 00:19:24.500
And so what that does is it reads and gets the data reactively.

00:19:24.500 --> 00:19:29.500
And you can specify within pin reactive read how often you want it to check.

00:19:29.500 --> 00:19:41.500
But anytime it notices that your pin has different data than before, it will automatically update and reflect that in your shiny app.

00:19:41.500 --> 00:19:46.500
Next, we have reactive values for storing filter data.

00:19:47.500 --> 00:19:56.500
We ensure that data is available and we store the filter data in a reactive values object.

00:19:56.500 --> 00:20:02.500
Next, we update filter choices based on the latest data.

00:20:02.500 --> 00:20:07.500
So, again, if I added a new category, I want to make sure that's reflected in the app itself.

00:20:07.500 --> 00:20:11.500
And then we dynamically render the filters based on the data.

00:20:12.500 --> 00:20:15.500
We set up the filters with the reactive data.

00:20:15.500 --> 00:20:20.500
And we update the filter data whenever the filters are applied.

00:20:22.500 --> 00:20:25.500
And then we render the calendar with filter data.

00:20:29.500 --> 00:20:32.500
Next, there's a few things for the calendar itself.

00:20:32.500 --> 00:20:35.500
Next, there's a few things for the calendar itself.

